---
layout: base.njk
pageClass: home
title: null
---

<section class="hero">
  <span class="hero__eyebrow">macOS · Apple Silicon · Open Source</span>
  <h1 class="hero__title">{{ site.title }}</h1>
  <p class="hero__tagline">{{ site.tagline }}</p>

  <div class="spectrum" aria-hidden="true">
    {% for _ in range(0, 15) %}<span class="spectrum__bar"></span>{% endfor %}
  </div>

  <div class="hero__cta">
    <a class="btn btn--primary" href="{{ site.release.latest_download }}">
      Download for {{ site.architecture }}
    </a>
    <a class="btn btn--secondary" href="{{ site.repo }}" rel="external noopener">
      View source
    </a>
  </div>
  <p class="hero__meta">
    Requires {{ site.minimumMacOS }}. Free. Notarised. No account needed.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="screenshots-marquee" aria-label="App screenshots">
  {%- set shots = [
    "Screenshot%202026-05-07%20at%2020.35.08.png",
    "Screenshot%202026-05-07%20at%2020.35.25.png",
    "Screenshot%202026-05-07%20at%2020.35.37.png",
    "Screenshot%202026-05-07%20at%2020.35.43.png",
    "Screenshot%202026-05-07%20at%2020.36.00.png",
    "Screenshot%202026-05-07%20at%2020.36.10.png",
    "Screenshot%202026-05-07%20at%2020.36.52.png",
    "Screenshot%202026-05-07%20at%2020.37.48.png"
  ] -%}
  <div class="marquee__track" aria-hidden="true">
    {%- for shot in shots %}
    <img class="marquee__img" src="/screenshots/{{ shot }}" alt="" loading="lazy">
    {%- endfor %}
    {# Duplicate for seamless loop #}
    {%- for shot in shots %}
    <img class="marquee__img" src="/screenshots/{{ shot }}" alt="" loading="lazy">
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--narrow">
  <p class="poke">
    Remember when you owned your music? When the player was a program on your
    computer, not a portal to a marketplace? When skipping a track took zero
    seconds, not three? Yeah. That.
  </p>
  <p>
    {{ site.title }} is a native macOS music player built for the kind of
    person who alphabetises their FLACs, has opinions about replay gain, and
    quietly judges anyone whose library is "in the cloud". It's free. It's
    fast. It plays _almost_ everything (not MIDI files). And it never, <em>ever</em>, tells anyone what
    you're listening to - unless you **want** it to.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>What it does</h2>
  <div class="features">
    {% for f in features %}
    <article class="feature">
      <h3>{{ f.title }}</h3>
      <p>{{ f.body }}</p>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--narrow">
  <h2>What it doesn't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Phone home. Ever.</li>
    <li>Ask you to sign in.</li>
    <li>Recommend playlists generated by people who don't know your name.</li>
    <li>Hide local files behind "Apple Music".</li>
    <li>Pretend the EQ does anything when it's set to "flat".</li>
    <li>Cost money.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="section section--narrow" style="text-align: center;">
  <h2>Get it.</h2>
  <p>
    <a class="btn btn--primary" href="{{ site.release.latest_download }}">
      Download {{ site.title }}
    </a>
  </p>
  <p class="hero__meta">
    Or browse <a href="{{ site.release.all_releases_url }}">all releases on GitHub</a>.
  </p>
</section>
